      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KRUMAC (3) raced handy then drove hard late but just missed last time out over a similar distance to this on the Gold Coast. Has been in work for a long while but continues to measure up. Looks the one to beat in the small field. QUEEN JEDDAH (6) enjoyed the step up in trip recently when beaten under a length over 1650m at Doomben. Should take a lot from that run and can make further progress here. COOL DRINKS (5) returned from a spell with a dominant maiden win over the mile at the Sunshine Coast last start. Lightly raced three-year-old who can go to the next level now. SWING STATE (1) rarely runs a bad race so must come into consideration despite a hefty 61.5 kg. PROBLEMATICAL (4) broke through last start but will find this a lot harder.",
